3. Strong Copyleft Obligations

The NFLv1 is a reciprocal license. To ensure the software remains free and open:


3.1 License Consistency: Any Derivative Work that you distribute or provide via SaaS must be licensed under this same License (NFLv1) or any later version of the NextFerret License. You may not impose further restrictions on the rights granted herein.

3.2 Source Code Availability: If you distribute the Work or a Derivative Work, you must make the complete, machine-readable source code available to the recipients, including any scripts or configuration files required to build and run the software.

3.3 Network Use (SaaS): Providing access to the software’s functionality via a network (SaaS) is considered Distribution under this License. You must make the source code of your version available to all users interacting with it.

